last_episode_to_air.name: History Lessons
last_episode_to_air.overview: Monkey and Bryce fight Boone throughout history, and ultimately Monkey is forced to face his true origin. But just when they think they've won the day, Akiko returns to take revenge.

name: Marvel's Hit-Monkey
overview: After a high-profile political assassination goes sideways, an injured hitman hides out amongst a tribe of snow monkeys in the mountains of Japan.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In New York City, Monkey finds a path to escape his life of killing, while Bryce attempts to repair the damage to those he wronged in life. But what will it cost them to undo the past?

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: After a high-profile political assassination goes sideways, an injured hitman hides out amongst a tribe of snow monkeys in the mountains of Japan.

episodes.name: Bright Lights, Big City
episodes.overview: Monkey and Bryce arrive in Tokyo seeking revenge. But will the differences in their style doom the mission before it even begins?

episodes.name: Legend of the Drunken Monkey
episodes.overview: Monkey and Bryce investigate the evil General Kato. The trail leads to an underground casino, where Monkey embraces the human world while struggling to continue his mission.

episodes.name: The Code
episodes.overview: Monkey and Bryce break into a prison to hunt a mysterious villain known as The Accountant and Monkey squares off against the prison’s most dangerous inmate.

episodes.name: Run Monkey Run
episodes.overview: After the Yakuza put a price on Monkey’s head, he and Bryce must face off against a who’s who of the city’s most colorful assassins, and their greatest foe of all: Bryce’s ego.

episodes.name: The Long Goodbye
episodes.overview: Monkey and Bryce’s powerful target releases an army of doubles to throw them off his scent as Bryce tries to make peace with his past.

episodes.name: Sayonara Monkey
episodes.overview: After battling their toughest foe yet, Monkey & Bryce’s partnership finally comes apart at the seams.

episodes.name: Home Sweet Home
episodes.overview: Ditching Bryce, Monkey returns to his old hot-springs and attempts to join a new tribe. Meanwhile, Bryce is forced to relive the events that thrust him down the path of assassin-hood.

episodes.name: The End (1)
episodes.overview: A reunited Monkey and Bryce get some much needed help from a pair of unexpected friends. They head to their final target and discover a startling truth.

episodes.name: The End (2)
episodes.overview: As Monkey and Bryce near the end of their journey they struggle against obstacles of their own making.

episodes.name: Return to Sender
episodes.overview: Monkey makes a name for himself as a hitman in New York City while Bryce tries to reconnect with his daughter. But all that changes when Haruka arrives with Bonsai Master's sword.

episodes.name: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner?
episodes.overview: Monkey, Bryce, and Haruka break protocol, demanding to know who set them up. This leads them to a mysterious Member's Only club, where an unlikely assassin aids in their mission.

episodes.name: The Rope
episodes.overview: Monkey tries to save Haruka, while Bryce looks for a way to speak with Iris. But when their efforts lead them to the hyper-capable Assassin's Cooperative, a greater mission emerges...

episodes.name: Never Too Late
episodes.overview: Monkey, Bryce, and Haruka struggle against an enemy with the ability to see into the future.

episodes.name: Akiko
episodes.overview: Monkey is violently reunited with Akiko, while the rift with Bryce deepens. Meanwhile, Monkey's bonds with the Co-Op grows deeper, and Boone's tragic past comes to light.

episodes.name: The Estate
episodes.overview: Monkey, Bryce, Haruka, and The Co-Op visit The Shepherd's ranch estate to retrieve the final relic, but he and his wife aren't going down without a fight.

episodes.name: The Last Supper
episodes.overview: Bryce, Haruka, and Iris turn Eunice's beach house into a fortress, awaiting the Co-Op's invasion. But when Monkey shows up, it triggers a knock-down, drag-out fight.

episodes.name: Mind Mall
episodes.overview: A reluctant Bryce smuggles himself into Slyke's mind in order to rescue Monkey from a sadistic killer known as The Hunter.

episodes.name: The Concrete Jungle
episodes.overview: The Co-Op uses the reforged relic to unleash the full power of the natural world on New York City. It's up to our gang and a group of unlikely heroes to stop them from destroying all of humankind.

episodes.name: History Lessons
episodes.overview: Monkey and Bryce fight Boone throughout history, and ultimately Monkey is forced to face his true origin. But just when they think they've won the day, Akiko returns to take revenge.
